"'''You and Me'''" is a song by American [[Alternative rock|alternative]] band [[Lifehouse (band)|Lifehouse]]. It is the first single released from their eponymous third studio album, [[Lifehouse (album)|''Lifehouse'']]. The track was written by lead singer [[Jason Wade]] and American record producer [[Jude Cole]]. It was recorded and produced by [[John Alag<U+00ED>a]] at his home studio in [[Easton, Maryland]]. The song was first released via digital download on January 28, 2005. It was then solicited to [[Contemporary hit radio|mainstream]] radio on March 15, 2005. An extended wedding version of the song was then released on July 26, 2005. Musically, "You and Me" is a melodic [[pop rock]] song which, by today's standards, has a notably high emphasis on acoustics. It also contains influences of [[Adult album alternative|adult alternative]].

The song received positive reviews from critics, who noted that the song was more mellow and stripped-down than their previous singles. It became a commercial success, charting in the top five in the United States and also charting in Australia and New Zealand. On May 19, 2005, the song was certified Gold by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]] for selling more than 500,000 units in the United States. In 2005, it became the ninth most downloaded song, according to [[Nielsen SoundScan]]. Because of its success, it appeared as the number one song on ''Billboard'''s list of Top 40 Adult Pop Songs from 1996-2011 on March 16, 2011. A music video for the song premiered on [[MTV|MTV.com]] on March 21, 2005, and features a couple as Wade sings in a train station. "You and Me" has appeared on many television shows, including ''[[Smallville]]'', ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[The Vampire Diaries]]'', [[Cold Case (TV series)|''Cold Case'']] and ''[[Gavin & Stacey]]''.

==Background and release==
The song was written by Lifehouse lead singer [[Jason Wade]] and American record producer [[Jude Cole]].<ref name="Writing Credits">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r731633|pure_url=yes}}|title=Lifehouse &ndash; Lifehouse|publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]]|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> It was recorded and produced by [[John Alag<U+00ED>a]] at his home studio in [[Easton, Maryland]].<ref name="Producers">{{cite web|url=http://www.lifehousemusic.com/news/default.aspx?pg=320|title="You and Me" Longest Running Single on Current Billboard|publisher=[[Geffen Records]]|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> In an interview with [[MTV]], Wade explained his experience working with Alag<U+00ED>a, and said, "When we walked into John's house, we didn't know what to expect, and we get in there and the mixing board is in the living room, the B3 [organ] is in the kitchen and the piano is over there. And he's so nonchalant about all his stuff <U+2014> there'd be a triple-platinum [[Dave Matthews Band]] plaque sticking out from under the bed."<ref name="MTV Interview">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1499343/lifehouse-rebound-from-sophomore-jinx.jhtml|title=Aided By John Mayer's Producer, Lifehouse Rebound From Sophomore Jinz|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> "You and Me" was first released via digital download on January 28, 2005.<ref name="Digital Download Release">{{cite web|url=http://www.lifehousemusic.com/news/default.aspx?pg=363|title="You and Me" Available Now For Digital Download|publisher=Geffen Records|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> It was then solicited to [[Contemporary hit radio|mainstream]] radio on March 15, 2005.<ref name="Mainstream Release">{{cite web|url=http://www.fmqb.com/Article.asp?id=69239|title=FMQB: Radio Industry News, Music Industry Updates, Arbitron Ratings, Music News and more!|publisher=[[Friday Morning Quarterback|Friday Morning Quarterback Album Report Inc.]]|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> An extended wedding version of the song was released on July 26, 2005.<ref name="Wedding Version Release">{{cite web|url=http://www.lifehousemusic.com/discography/default.aspx?pid=1079|title=You and Me (Extended Wedding Song Version)|publisher=Geffen Records|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>

==Composition and critical reception==
"You and Me" was described as a [[pop rock]] song with influences of [[adult album alternative|adult alternative]].<ref name="Genre">{{cite web|url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/lifehouse/albums/you-and-me--197864610|title=You and Me by Lifehouse|publisher=[[Yahoo! Music]]|accessdate=2011-08-05}}</ref> John DiBiase of [[Jesus Freak Hideout]] described the song as "a tender acoustic love ballad" noting how the song was "noticeably more mellow and stripped-down than the band's previous singles."<ref name="Jesus Freak Hideout">{{cite web|url=http://www.jesusfreakhideout.com/cdreviews/Lifehouse.asp|title=Lifehouse, "Lifehouse" Review|last=DiBiase|first=John|publisher=[[Jesus Freak Hideout]]|accessdate=2011-07-09}}</ref> [[Ultimate Guitar]] called the song "a tender love-ballad" and noted how it would be "a perfect soundtrack for a wedding."<ref name="Ultimate Guitar">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/reviews/compact_discs/lifehouse/lifehouse/index.html|title=Lifehouse Review|publisher=[[Ultimate Guitar]]|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> Alternative Addiction said that the song was embraced by fans in the same way "[[Hanging by a Moment]]" was when Lifehouse started as a band.<ref name="Alternative Addiction">{{cite web|url=http://www.alternativeaddiction.com/newmusic/exec/albumreviews.asp?id=114|title=Review of "Lifehouse" by Lifehouse|publisher=Alternative Addiction LLC|accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref> According to the sheet music published at Musicnotes.com by [[Sony/ATV Music Publishing]], the song is set in [[Time signature#Most frequent time signatures|6/8]] time with a "slow" tempo of 46 [[beats per minute]].<ref name="Composition">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0052641&|title=Lifehouse &ndash; You and Me Sheet Music (Digital Download)|accessdate=2011-08-04|publisher=[[Sony/ATV Music Publishing]]}}</ref> It is composed in the key of [[G major]] with Wade's vocal range spanning from the low-note of C<sub>3</sub> to the high-note of E<sub>4</sub>.<ref name="Composition"/> The song has a basic [[chord progression]] of G<sub>5</sub><U+2013>G<sub>5</sub>/C<U+2013>G<sub>5</sub>/F{{music|sharp}}<U+2013>G<sub>5</sub>/B<U+2013>Em<sub>7</sub><U+2013>D<sub>sus4</sub><U+2013>C.<ref name="Composition"/>

==Chart performance==
"You and Me" debuted at number 92 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] for the week of February 12, 2005.<ref name="Debut">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=all}}|title=You and Me &ndash; Lifehouse|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> It stayed on the chart for 62 non-consecutive weeks, and eventually peaked at number five.<ref name="Hot 100">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=all}}|title=Lifehouse Album & Song Chart History (Hot 100)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> On the ''Billboard'' [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] chart, the song debuted at number 29 for the week of July 23, 2005.<ref name="Debut"/> It eventually peaked at number one after it stayed on the chart for 34 non-consecutive weeks.<ref name="Adult Contemporary">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=Adult Contemporary}}|title=Lifehouse Album & Song Chart History (Adult Contemporary)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> The song debuted at number 29 on the ''Billboard'' [[Adult Top 40|Adult Pop Songs]] chart for the week of February 19, 2005.<ref name="Debut"/> After moving around the chart for 39 consecutive weeks, the song peaked at number one for nine non-consecutive weeks.<ref name="Adult Pop Songs">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=Adult Pop Songs}}|title=Lifehouse Album & Song Chart History (Adult Pop Songs)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> Because of its success on the chart, "You and Me" became the number one song on ''Billboard'''s list of the Top 40 Adult Pop Songs from 1996-2011 on March 16, 2011.<ref name="Adult Pop Songs History">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/472495/the-top-40-adult-pop-songs|title=The Top 40 Adult Pop Songs (1996-2011)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Prometheus Global Media}}</ref> On the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Digital Songs|Digital Songs]] chart, the song debuted at number 38 for the week of April 23, 2005.<ref name="Debut"/> After moving around the chart for 31 non-consecutive weeks, the song eventually peaked at number three.<ref name="Digital Songs">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=Digital Songs}}|title=Lifehouse Album & Song Chart History (Digital Songs)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> "You and Me" debuted at number 37 on the ''Billboard'' [[Pop Songs]] chart during the week of May 21, 2005.<ref name="Debut"/> It eventually peaked at number four after it spent 26 consecutive weeks on the chart.<ref name="Pop Songs">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=Pop Songs B}}|title=Lifehouse Album & Song Chart History (Pop Songs)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> On the ''Billboard'' [[Hot 100 Airplay (Radio Songs)|Radio Songs]] chart, the track debuted at number 74 during the week of May 21, 2005.<ref name="Debut"/> It proceeded to move around the chart for 26 consecutive weeks, until it eventually peaked at number nine.<ref name="Radio Songs">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=lifehouse|chart=Radio Songs}}|title=Lifehouse Album & Song Chart History (Radio Songs)|work=Billboard|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Nielsen Business Media}}</ref> According to [[Nielsen SoundScan]], "You and Me" was the ninth top selling digital song of 2005.<ref name="Digital Songs of 2005">{{cite web|url=http://www.lifehousemusic.com/news/default.aspx?pg=329|title=Lifehouse In Top 2005 Downloads|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=[[Geffen Records]]}}</ref> On May 19, 2005, "You and Me" was certified Gold by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]] for selling more than 500,000 units of the song.<ref name="Gold Certification">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Lifehouse&format=SINGLE&go=Search&perPage=25|title=RIAA &ndash; Recording Industry Association of America|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]}}</ref>

The song also managed to achieve international success. In Australia, the song debuted at number 30 on the [[ARIA Charts]] for the week of May 29, 2005. That later became its peak after it spent four weeks on the chart.<ref name="Australia">{{cite web|url=http://www.australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Lifehouse&titel=You+And+Me&cat=s|title=australian-charts.com &ndash; Lifehouse &ndash; You And Me|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Hung Medien}}</ref> On the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]], "You and Me" debuted at number 39, which later became its peak after it spent only one week on the chart during the week of October 31, 2005.<ref name="New Zealand">{{cite web|url=http://charts.org.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Lifehouse&titel=You+And+Me&cat=s|title=charts.org.nz &ndash; Lifehouse &ndash; You And Me|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=Hung Medien}}</ref>

==Television appearances==
On April 20, 2005, Lifehouse made an appearance in the ''[[Smallville]]'' episode "Spirit" and performed "You and Me" among other songs.<ref name="Smallville">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/smallville/spirit/episode/396153/trivia.html|title=Smallville: Spirit Trivia & Quotes &ndash; TV.com|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref> 
It also appeared in the ''[[The 4400]]'' episode "Life Interrupted" on July 17, 2005.<ref name="The 4400">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/the-4400/life-interrupted/episode/406603/summary.html|title=The 4400: Life Interrupted Episode Summary &ndash; TV.com|accessdate=2011-08-06|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref> Several months later, "You and Me" also made an appearance in the ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'''s episode "Much Too Much" that premiered on November 27, 2005.<ref name="Grey's Anatomy">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/greys-anatomy/much-too-much/episode/497678/summary.html|title=Grey's Anatomy: Much Too Much Episode Summary &ndash; TV.com|accessdate=2011-08-06|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref> The song appeared in the ''[[Everwood]]'' episode "Getting to Know You" on December 8, 2005 and in the [[Cold Case (TV series)|''Cold Case'']] episode "One Night" on March 19, 2006.<ref name="Everwood">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/everwood/getting-to-know-you/episode/531221/trivia.html|title=Everwood: Getting to Know You Trivia & Quotes &ndash; TV.com|accessdate=2011-08-06|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref><ref name="Cold">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/cold-case/one-night/episode/625525/trivia.html|title=Cold Case: One Night Trivia & Quotes &ndash; TV.com|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref> On May 13, 2007, the song appeared in the pilot episode of ''[[Gavin & Stacey]]''.<ref name="Gavin & Stacey">{{cite web|url=http://www.tv.com/gavin-and-stacey/episode-one/episode/1087424/summary.html|title=Gavin and Stacey: Episode One Episode Summary &ndash; TV.com|accessdate=2011-08-06|publisher=CBS Interactive}}</ref>

==Music video==
===Background===
<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:You and Me Music Video.png|thumb|220px|right|Wade plays the guitar and sings as Lifehouse bassist Bryce Soderburg (left) and drummer Rick Woolstenhulme Jr. (right) sit at the Los Angeles Union Station.]] -->
The music video, directed by Bill Yukich, premiered on [[MTV|MTV.com]] on March 21, 2005.<ref name="Music Video Release">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/videos/lifehouse/52948/you-and-me.jhtml6|title=Lifehouse - "You and Me"|accessdate=2011-08-06|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]}}</ref> It was then released on [[iTunes]] for digital download on March 30, 2005.<ref name="Music Video Digital Release">{{cite web|url=http://itunes.apple.com/us/music-video/you-and-me/id81531166|title=You and Me by Lifehouse|accessdate=2011-08-05|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]}}</ref>

===Synopsis===
The video starts with a woman exiting the taxi and going to the [[Los Angeles Union Station]]. A man exits a car and follows her. Wade then plays the first verse and first chorus in the [[waiting area]] of the L. A. Union Station. As the band plays the second verse, they are shown playing at the rooftop with [[Iron Mountain (Los Angeles County)|Iron Mountain]] clearly visible. When the chorus plays again, they are shown at the roof with lights from the buildings of Los Angeles at night. When Wade sings the bridge, he is on the roof of the [[Roosevelt Hotel (Hollywood)|Roosevelt Hotel]] in [[Hollywood Boulevard]]. The man and the woman are also seen running in the boarding area of the Los Angeles Union Station. They later meet up and kiss in one of the boarding platforms of the station in front of a train which later starts to move. The video ends with the band sitting down in the waiting hall.

